22 ID_List str2list(m_str path, m_uint* array_depth )
23 {
24  m_uint len = 0;
25  m_int i, j;
26  char curr[256];
27  ID_List list = NULL;
28  char last = '\0';
29  m_uint depth = 0;
30  memset(curr, 0, 256);
31  while(path[len] != '\0')
32  len++;
33 
34  while(len > 2 && path[len - 1] == ']' && path[len - 2] == '[') {
35  depth++;
36  len -= 2;
37  }
38 
39  for(i = len - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
40  char c = path[i];
41  if(c != '.') {
42  if( (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z')
43  || (c == '_') || (c >= '0' && c <= '9') || (i == 0 && c == '@'))
44  curr[i] = c;
45  else {
46  err_msg(UTIL_, 0, "illegal character '%c' in path '%s'...", c, path);
47  free_ID_List(list);
48  return NULL;
49  }
50  }
51  if(c == '.' || i == 0) {
52  if((i != 0 && last != '.' && last != '\0') ||
53  (i == 0 && c != '.')) {
54  m_int size = strlen(curr);
55  for(j = 0; j < size / 2; j++) {
56  char s = curr[j];
57  curr[j] = curr[size - j - 1];
58  curr[size - j - 1] = s;
59  }
60  list = prepend_id_list(curr, list, 0);
61  memset(curr, 0, sizeof(curr));
62  } else {
63  err_msg(UTIL_, 0, "path '%s' must not begin or end with '.'", path);
64  free_ID_List(list);
65  return NULL;
66  }
67  }
68  last = c;
69  }
70  path = strndup(path, len);
71  list->xid = insert_symbol(path);
72  if(array_depth)
73  *array_depth = depth;
74  free(path);
75  return list;
76 }

78 static m_bool mk_xtor(Type type, m_uint d, e_native_func e) {
79  VM_Code* code;
80  m_str name, filename;
81  if(e == NATIVE_CTOR) {
82  type->has_constructor = 1;
83  name = "ctor";
84  filename = "[internal ctor definition]";
85  code = &type->info->pre_ctor;
86  } else {
87  type->has_destructor = 1;
88  name = type->name;
89  filename = "[internal dtor definition]";
90  code = &type->info->dtor;
91  }
92  *code = new_VM_Code(NULL, SZ_INT, 1, name, filename);
93  (*code)->native_func = (m_uint)d;
94  (*code)->native_func_type = e;
95  return 1;
96 }

158 static m_int import_var(Env env, const m_str type, const m_str name,
159  const m_bool is_static, const m_bool is_const, const m_bool is_ref, m_uint* addr, const m_str doc) {
160  m_int ret = -1;
161  m_uint array_depth;
162  ID_List path;
163  Type_Decl* type_decl;
164  Var_Decl var_decl;
165  Var_Decl_List var_decl_list;
166  Expression exp_decl;
167  CHECK_EB(env->class_def)
168  if(!(path = str2list(type, &array_depth))) {
169  err_msg(TYPE_, 0, "... during mvar import '%s.%s'...", env->class_def->name, name );
170  return -1;
171  }
172 
173  type_decl = new_Type_Decl(path, is_ref, 0);
174  if(array_depth) {
175  type_decl->array = new_array_sub(NULL, 0);
176  type_decl->array->depth = array_depth;
177  }
178  var_decl = new_Var_Decl(name, NULL, 0);
179  if(array_depth) {
180  var_decl->array = new_array_sub(NULL, 0);
181  var_decl->array->depth = array_depth;
182  }
183  var_decl_list = new_Var_Decl_List(var_decl, NULL, 0);
184  exp_decl = new_Decl_Expression(type_decl, var_decl_list, 0, 0);
185  var_decl->addr = (void *)addr;
186  if(scan1_Decl_Expression(env, exp_decl->d.exp_decl) < 0)
187  goto error;
188  if(scan2_Decl_Expression(env, exp_decl->d.exp_decl) < 0)
189  goto error;
190  var_decl->value->is_const = is_const;
191  if(!check_Decl_Expression(env, exp_decl->d.exp_decl))
192  goto error;
193 
194  if(doc)
195  var_decl->value->doc = doc;
196  var_decl->value->is_import = 1;
197  ret = var_decl->value->offset;
198 error:
199  free_Expression(exp_decl);
200  return ret;
201 }

209 static Arg_List make_dll_arg_list(DL_Func * dl_fun)
210 {
211  Arg_List arg_list = NULL;
212  Type_Decl* type_decl = NULL;
213  Var_Decl var_decl = NULL;
214  ID_List type_path = NULL;
215  ID_List type_path2 = NULL;
216 // ID_List name_path = NULL;
217  Array_Sub array_sub = NULL;
218  DL_Value* arg = NULL;
219  m_uint array_depth = 0;
220  m_uint array_depth2 = 0;
221  m_int i = 0, j;
222 
223  for(i = vector_size(dl_fun->args) - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
224  array_depth = array_depth2 = 0;
225  array_sub = NULL;
226  arg = (DL_Value*)vector_at(dl_fun->args, i);
227  type_path = str2list(arg->type, &array_depth);
228  if(!type_path) {
229  err_msg(TYPE_, 0, "...at argument '%i'...", i + 1 );
230  free_Vector(dl_fun->args);
231  if(arg_list)
232  free_Arg_List(arg_list);
233  return NULL;
234  }
235  type_decl = new_Type_Decl( type_path, 0, 0 );
236  type_path2 = str2list(arg->name, &array_depth2 );
237  free_ID_List(type_path2);
238  if(array_depth && array_depth2) {
239  err_msg(TYPE_, 0, "array subscript specified incorrectly for built-in module" );
240  // TODO: cleanup
241  free_Type_Decl(type_decl);
242  if(arg_list)
243  free_Arg_List(arg_list);
244  return NULL;
245  }
246  // TODO: arrays?
247  if(array_depth2)
248  array_depth = array_depth2;
249  if(array_depth) {
250  array_sub = new_array_sub( NULL, 0 );
251  for(j = 1; j < array_depth; j++ )
252  array_sub = prepend_array_sub( array_sub, NULL, 0 );
253  }
254  var_decl = new_Var_Decl(arg->name, array_sub, 0 );
255  arg_list = new_Arg_List( type_decl, var_decl, arg_list, 0 );
256  arg_list->doc = arg->doc;
257  free_DL_Value(arg); /* could be free(arg) */
258  }
259  return arg_list;
260 }

309 #define CHECK_FN(a) if(a < 0) { if(func_def->func) rem_ref(func_def->func->obj, func_def->func); free_Func_Def(func_def); return NULL;}
310 static Func import_fun(Env env, DL_Func * mfun, m_bool is_static) {
311  Func_Def func_def;
312  CHECK_OO(mfun) // probably deserve an err msg
313  CHECK_EO(env->class_def)

315  CHECK_FN(scan1_Func_Def(env, func_def))
